This is the NCCC app. Read `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root for full conventions. The summary:

- Private PWA for the Norton Commons Cigar Club (12 members). Not a public app.
- Stack: Next.js 16 (App Router, RSC, Server Actions), Supabase, Tailwind v4, TypeScript.
- Models: `gpt-5-mini` for vision + pairing prose, `gpt-5-nano` for chip→wheel mapping.

Honor the design system in `docs/design-system.md`:
- Brass is the ONE primary-action color per screen.
- Ember is for lit recommend icons only.
- Moss is for club-validated pairing markers only.
- Etched section dividers (`<Divider label="..." />`) at every major break.
- The Bartender (italic Playfair, `<Voice />`) appears at empty states + recommendations only.

Identity convention: member display ALWAYS uses `formatMemberName(user)` → `"First L"`. Two Pauls in the club.

The flavor wheel is silent infrastructure. Never render sliders. Only aggregated tag clouds.

Prefer Server Components + Server Actions. Default to `import type` for types. Self-documenting names over comments.

Phase status lives in `planning/nccc-implementation-plan.md` — read before adding features outside the current phase.
